*TITR
test with two nested frames that are forced to have the same defining helmert paramaters.
to go from (1 0 0) (coord of point Z in subframe) to (0 0 1) (coord of Z in rootframe) with a RY rotation needs 100 gon.
As both SLAVE frames are nested and forced to be equal, they will divide the 100 gon rotation into two equal 50 gon rotations.
*OLOC
*CONSI
*APRI
*PREC 6
*INSTR
*CALA
Z 0 0 1
*FRAME SLAVE_1 0 0 0 0 0 0 1 RY 
*FRAME SLAVE_2 0 0 0 0 0 0 1 RY 
*OBSXYZ 
Z 1 0 0 1.00 1.00 1.00
*ENDFRAME
*ENDFRAME
*END
